dc_description_s: This polygon shapefile represents the Claiborne Corridor for New Orleans, LA in 2017. The Network for Economic Opportunity is an initiative of the City of New Orleans, founded to establish productive partnerships among local industries, small businesses, residents, non-profits, philanthropy, and city agencies to achieve common goals within six priority areas: Economic Opportunity, Housing Affordability, Cultural Preservation, Transportation Access, Sustainable Environment, and Safe & Healthy Neighborhoods. The Network manages the connections. Local industries and Claiborne Corridor residents activate the goals. Cross-sector partners enable the work. The Claiborne Corridor hosts the pilot programs and projects that emerge to help New Orleanians gain a robust and enduring urban core. This file was downloaded on December, 2018 by NYU Data Services. It was originally represented on the New Orleans Open Data Socrata portal as catalog record 9zkz-jw88
